=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains a summary of an app authorization.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> App => Str

The name of the application.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AppAuthorizationArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the app authorization.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AppBundleArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the app bundle for the app
authorization.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Status => Str

The state of the app authorization.

The following states are possible:

=over

=item *

C<PendingConnect>: The initial state of the app authorization. The app
authorization is created but not yet connected.

=item *

C<Connected>: The app authorization is connected to the application,
and is ready to be used.

=item *

C<ConnectionValidationFailed>: The app authorization received a
validation exception when trying to connect to the application. If the
app authorization is in this state, you should verify the configured
credentials and try to connect the app authorization again.

=item *

C<TokenAutoRotationFailed>: AppFabric failed to refresh the access
token. If the app authorization is in this state, you should try to
reconnect the app authorization.

=back



=head2 B<REQUIRED> Tenant => L<Paws::AppFabric::Tenant>

Contains information about an application tenant, such as the
application display name and identifier.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> UpdatedAt => Str

Timestamp for when the app authorization was last updated.



